<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8" standalone="yes"?><rss version="2.0" xmlns:atom="http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom"><channel><title>API Test on Splunk Observability Cloud Workshops</title><link>https://splunk.github.io/observability-workshop/en/ninja-workshops/instrumentation/4-synthetics-scripting/2-api-test/</link><description>Recent content in API Test on Splunk Observability Cloud Workshops</description><generator>Hugo</generator><language>en</language><atom:link href="https://splunk.github.io/observability-workshop/en/ninja-workshops/instrumentation/4-synthetics-scripting/2-api-test/index.xml" rel="self" type="application/rss+xml"/><item><title>Global Variables</title><link>https://splunk.github.io/observability-workshop/en/ninja-workshops/instrumentation/4-synthetics-scripting/2-api-test/1-global-varilables/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://splunk.github.io/observability-workshop/en/ninja-workshops/instrumentation/4-synthetics-scripting/2-api-test/1-global-varilables/</guid><description>&lt;h2 id="global-variables"&gt;
 &lt;span class="heading-text"&gt;Global Variables&lt;/span&gt;
 &lt;a class="heading-anchor" href="#global-variables" aria-label="Permalink" aria-hidden="true"&gt;#&lt;/a&gt;
&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;View the global variable that we&amp;rsquo;ll use to perform our API test. Click on &lt;strong&gt;Global Variables&lt;/strong&gt; under the cog. The global variable named &lt;code&gt;env.encoded_auth&lt;/code&gt; will be the one that we&amp;rsquo;ll use to build the spotify API transaction.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;figure class="figure"&gt;
 &lt;div class="figure__inner"&gt;
 &lt;img src="../../img/global-variables.png" alt="placeholder" loading="lazy" decoding="async"&gt;
 &lt;/div&gt;
 
&lt;/figure&gt;
&lt;/p&gt;</description></item><item><title>Create new API test</title><link>https://splunk.github.io/observability-workshop/en/ninja-workshops/instrumentation/4-synthetics-scripting/2-api-test/2-create-new-check/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://splunk.github.io/observability-workshop/en/ninja-workshops/instrumentation/4-synthetics-scripting/2-api-test/2-create-new-check/</guid><description>&lt;h2 id="create-a-new-api-test"&gt;
 &lt;span class="heading-text"&gt;Create a new API test&lt;/span&gt;
 &lt;a class="heading-anchor" href="#create-a-new-api-test" aria-label="Permalink" aria-hidden="true"&gt;#&lt;/a&gt;
&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Create a new API test by clicking on the &lt;button class="btn-inline btn-inline--filled" type="button" style="--btn-color: #1d5d99"&gt;&lt;span&gt;Add new test&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/button&gt; button and select &lt;strong&gt;API test&lt;/strong&gt; from the dropdown. Name the test using &lt;strong&gt;your initials&lt;/strong&gt; followed by &lt;strong&gt;Spotify API&lt;/strong&gt; e.g. &lt;strong&gt;RWC - Spotify API&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;figure class="figure"&gt;
 &lt;div class="figure__inner"&gt;
 &lt;img src="../../img/new-api-check.png" alt="placeholder" loading="lazy" decoding="async"&gt;
 &lt;/div&gt;
 
&lt;/figure&gt;
&lt;/p&gt;</description></item><item><title>Authentication Request</title><link>https://splunk.github.io/observability-workshop/en/ninja-workshops/instrumentation/4-synthetics-scripting/2-api-test/3-authentication-request/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://splunk.github.io/observability-workshop/en/ninja-workshops/instrumentation/4-synthetics-scripting/2-api-test/3-authentication-request/</guid><description>&lt;h2 id="add-authentication-request"&gt;
 &lt;span class="heading-text"&gt;Add Authentication Request&lt;/span&gt;
 &lt;a class="heading-anchor" href="#add-authentication-request" aria-label="Permalink" aria-hidden="true"&gt;#&lt;/a&gt;
&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Click on &lt;button class="btn-inline" type="button"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Add requests&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/button&gt; and enter the request step name e.g. &lt;strong&gt;Authenticate with Spotify API&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;figure class="figure"&gt;
 &lt;div class="figure__inner"&gt;
 &lt;img src="../../img/add-request.png" alt="placeholder" loading="lazy" decoding="async"&gt;
 &lt;/div&gt;
 
&lt;/figure&gt;
&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Expand the Request section, from the drop-down change the request method to &lt;strong&gt;POST&lt;/strong&gt; and enter the following URL:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class="code-block"&gt;
 &lt;div class="code-block__header"&gt;
 &lt;span class="code-block__file"&gt;&lt;span class="code-block__lang"&gt;text&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;
 &lt;button class="code-block__copy" type="button" aria-label="Copy code to clipboard"&gt;Copy&lt;/button&gt;
 &lt;/div&gt;
 &lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" class="chroma"&gt;&lt;code class="language-text" data-lang="text"&gt;&lt;span class="line"&gt;&lt;span class="cl"&gt;https://accounts.spotify.com/api/token&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;In the &lt;strong&gt;Payload body&lt;/strong&gt; section enter the following:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class="code-block"&gt;
 &lt;div class="code-block__header"&gt;
 &lt;span class="code-block__file"&gt;&lt;span class="code-block__lang"&gt;text&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;
 &lt;button class="code-block__copy" type="button" aria-label="Copy code to clipboard"&gt;Copy&lt;/button&gt;
 &lt;/div&gt;
 &lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" class="chroma"&gt;&lt;code class="language-text" data-lang="text"&gt;&lt;span class="line"&gt;&lt;span class="cl"&gt;grant_type=client_credentials&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Next, add two request headers with the following key/value pairings:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;CONTENT-TYPE: application/x-www-form-urlencoded&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;AUTHORIZATION: Basic {{env.encoded_auth}}&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Expand the &lt;strong&gt;Validation&lt;/strong&gt; section and add the following extraction:&lt;/p&gt;</description></item><item><title>Search Request</title><link>https://splunk.github.io/observability-workshop/en/ninja-workshops/instrumentation/4-synthetics-scripting/2-api-test/4-search-request/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://splunk.github.io/observability-workshop/en/ninja-workshops/instrumentation/4-synthetics-scripting/2-api-test/4-search-request/</guid><description>&lt;h2 id="add-search-request"&gt;
 &lt;span class="heading-text"&gt;Add Search Request&lt;/span&gt;
 &lt;a class="heading-anchor" href="#add-search-request" aria-label="Permalink" aria-hidden="true"&gt;#&lt;/a&gt;
&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Click on &lt;button class="btn-inline" type="button"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Add Request&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/button&gt; to add the next step. Name the step &lt;strong&gt;Search for Tracks named &amp;ldquo;Up around the bend&amp;rdquo;&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Expand the &lt;strong&gt;Request&lt;/strong&gt; section and change the request method to &lt;strong&gt;GET&lt;/strong&gt; and enter the following URL:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class="code-block"&gt;
 &lt;div class="code-block__header"&gt;
 &lt;span class="code-block__file"&gt;&lt;span class="code-block__lang"&gt;text&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;
 &lt;button class="code-block__copy" type="button" aria-label="Copy code to clipboard"&gt;Copy&lt;/button&gt;
 &lt;/div&gt;
 &lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" class="chroma"&gt;&lt;code class="language-text" data-lang="text"&gt;&lt;span class="line"&gt;&lt;span class="cl"&gt;https://api.spotify.com/v1/search?q=Up%20around%20the%20bend&amp;amp;type=track&amp;amp;offset=0&amp;amp;limit=5&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Next, add two request headers with the following key/value pairings:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;CONTENT-TYPE: application/json&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;AUTHORIZATION: Bearer {{custom.access_token}}&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;figure class="figure"&gt;
 &lt;div class="figure__inner"&gt;
 &lt;img src="../../img/add-search-request.png" alt="Add search request" loading="lazy" decoding="async"&gt;
 &lt;/div&gt;
 
&lt;/figure&gt;
&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Expand the &lt;strong&gt;Validation&lt;/strong&gt; section and add the following extraction:&lt;/p&gt;</description></item><item><title>View results</title><link>https://splunk.github.io/observability-workshop/en/ninja-workshops/instrumentation/4-synthetics-scripting/2-api-test/5-view-results/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://splunk.github.io/observability-workshop/en/ninja-workshops/instrumentation/4-synthetics-scripting/2-api-test/5-view-results/</guid><description>&lt;h2 id="view-results"&gt;
 &lt;span class="heading-text"&gt;View results&lt;/span&gt;
 &lt;a class="heading-anchor" href="#view-results" aria-label="Permalink" aria-hidden="true"&gt;#&lt;/a&gt;
&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Wait for a few minutes for the test to provision and run. Once you see the test has run successfully, click on the run to view the test results:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;figure class="figure"&gt;
 &lt;div class="figure__inner"&gt;
 &lt;img src="../../img/api-test-result.png" alt="API test result" loading="lazy" decoding="async"&gt;
 &lt;/div&gt;
 
&lt;/figure&gt;
&lt;/p&gt;
